            <div class="card-brutal p-8 md:p-12">
                <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-8 md:mb-12 text-center font-display uppercase tracking-tight">Our Philosophy</h3>
                
                <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-8 text-sm md:text-base">
                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 text-black dark:text-white">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display">▲ Free to use, periodt.</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We're not here to milk your wallet. AetherMeet is free and will stay free because we're not monsters.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 text-black dark:text-white">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display">■ We don't store your room passwords and honestly don't want to.</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Your passwords = your business. We're just here to vibe check that they're real dictionary words. That's it, that's the tweet.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 text-black dark:text-white">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display">◆ If hackers somehow breach our entire server...</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Your rooms are still unreadable because only you hold the passwords to find and decrypt them (assuming you didn't use "password123" like a boomer).</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 text-black dark:text-white">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display">▼ If the government wants to read our database...</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Your rooms are still unreadable because we literally can't decrypt them without your passwords. We're not snitches AND we're technically unable to snitch. Win-win fr.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 text-black dark:text-white">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display">● We don't care what you chat about...</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Because we literally don't know and can't check. Only you hold the room codes and passwords. Keep it legal though, broos.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 text-black dark:text-white">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display">◯ If you find a room with your content...</p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Just delete it yourself broo. If you can find it, you can edit it. Democracy in action</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card-brutal p-4 md:p-6 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-950/20 text-red-700 dark:text-red-300" style="border-color: #EF4444; box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset) var(--shadow-offset) 0px #EF4444;">
                        <p class="font-extrabold text-base md:text-lg mb-2 font-display text-red-800 dark:text-red-400">▲ We are NOT responsible for:</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
                            <li>If you use a room password like "1234" and someone else accesses it (that's on you broo)</li>
                            <li>If someone randomly guesses your "totally unique" password and finds your room (probability is not our problem)</li>
                            <li>If a meteor hits our servers or aliens steal our hard drives (we backup everything but acts of God/aliens are beyond our pay grade)</li>
                            <li>Your poor life choices in general (we provide the platform, you provide the drama)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="text-center mt-8">
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-mono text-sm">
                            TLDR: We built this for you, not against you. Don't be dumb with passwords and we'll all be fine. 
                            <br>
                            No cap. ▣
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
